# sundae_bar — Cursor Rules for Frontend Development

This file provides conventions and patterns for the sundae_bar codebase. Follow these rules when generating or modifying frontend code.

## Project Structure

This is a **Turborepo monorepo**. All frontend work happens inside `apps/web/`.

```
sundae-bar/
├── apps/
│   ├── web/          # Next.js web app (port 3000) — YOUR WORK GOES HERE
│   └── studio/       # Sanity Studio CMS (port 3333)
├── packages/
│   ├── eslint-config/
│   └── typescript-config/
└── turbo.json
```

**Path alias:** `@/` resolves to `apps/web/` (configured in `tsconfig.json`).

```tsx
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"; // → apps/web/lib/utils.ts
```

---

## File & Naming Conventions

- **All files and folders:** `kebab-case` — `agent-card.tsx`, `use-mobile.ts`, `components/about/`
- **No PascalCase filenames** — only component/function exports use PascalCase
- **Page files:** always `page.tsx`, layouts `layout.tsx`, loading `loading.tsx`, error `error.tsx`, not-found `not-found.tsx`
- **Component files:** named export matching the component — `export function AgentCard()` in `agent-card.tsx`
- **Hook files:** prefixed with `use-` — `use-mobile.ts`, `use-auth.ts`

---

## Import Ordering

Imports are organized in groups separated by blank lines. Always follow this order:

```tsx
"use client"; // 1. Directive (if needed)

import { useState } from "react"; // 2. React / Next.js imports
import Image from "next/image";
import Link from "next/link";

import { ArrowRight, X } from "lucide-react"; // 3. External libraries
import { motion } from "motion/react";

import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"; // 4. Internal @/ imports (lib, hooks, components, constants)
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";

import { SectionLabel } from "./section-label"; // 5. Relative imports
```

---

## Component Organization

### Root `/components` — Global components used across the app

Flat files for shared UI: `header.tsx`, `footer.tsx`, `logo.tsx`, `banner-image.tsx`, `newsletter-form.tsx`, `social-icons.tsx`, etc.

### Feature folders — Components scoped to a feature

```
components/about/        — About page (section-label, scroll-reveal-text, team-section)
components/agents/       — Agent cards, detail views
components/blog/         — Blog cards, portable text, Sanity image
components/chat/         — AI chat interface
components/dashboard/    — Dashboard sidebar, listings, billing
components/enterprise/   — Enterprise page components
components/explore/      — Search, filters, explore grid
components/forms/        — Form UIs organized by feature subdirectory
components/homepage/     — Hero, Intro, FeaturedListings, HowItWorks, etc.
components/lab/          — Subnet validation lab
components/listings/     — Listing thumbnails, banners
components/products/     — Product cards/details (prompts, workflows)
components/ui/           — shadcn/ui base components (customized — see below)
```

**Rule:** Place new components in the appropriate feature folder. Only put truly shared/global components at the root level.

---

## Route Groups (`apps/web/app/`)

Next.js App Router with route groups for logical separation:

| Group | Purpose | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `(frontend)` | Public pages: `/`, `/explore`, `/about`, `/terms-of-service` | No auth |
| `(auth)` | `/login`, `/sign-up`, `/reset-password` | Redirect if already authed |
| `(backend)` | `/dashboard/**` | Protected — requires login |
| `(agent-portal)` | `/agent-portal/**` — AI chat | Protected |
| `(lab)` | `/lab/**` — Subnet 121 validation | Protected |
| `(news)` | `/news/**` — Blog (Sanity CMS) | Public |

---

## Styling System

### Tailwind CSS v4

- Config is defined in `apps/web/app/globals.css` via `@theme {}` — there is **no `tailwind.config.ts`** in `apps/web/`
- Plugins: `@tailwindcss/typography`, `tailwindcss-animate`

### Fonts

| Font | Variable | Tailwind class | Usage |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Geist Sans** | `--font-geist-sans` | `font-sans` (default) | All body text and UI |
| **JetBrains Mono** | `--jetbrains-mono` | `font-mono` | Section labels, eyebrows, footer headings, code, captions |

Both are loaded in `app/layout.tsx` via `next/font`.

### Color System

**All standard Tailwind colors are wiped** (`--color-*: initial`). Only brand colors exist.

**Brand palette** (use these directly when needed):
- Grays: `gray-100` through `gray-700`
- Navy: `navy-100` through `navy-800` (dark blue-grays for dark sections)
- Blue: `blue-100`, `blue-300`, `blue-400`, `blue-700`
- Purple: `purple-50`, `purple-100`, `purple-200`, `purple-300`
- Orange: `orange-100`, `orange-200`, `orange-300`
- Teal: `teal-200`, `teal-300`, `teal-400`
- Green: `green-100`, `green-200`, `green-300`, `green-400`
- Red: `red-100`, `red-200`, `red-400`, `red-600`
- Pink: `pink-300`
- Special: `light-blue` (near-white blue for gradients), `white`, `black`

**Semantic tokens** (prefer these in components):

| Token | Maps to | Usage |
|---|---|---|
| `background` / `foreground` | white / navy-600 | Page background / default text |
| `background-secondary` | gray-100 | Card/section backgrounds |
| `primary` / `primary-foreground` | purple-300 / white | Main CTAs, buttons |
| `secondary` / `secondary-foreground` | blue-300 / black | Secondary actions |
| `tertiary` / `tertiary-foreground` | orange-200 / black | Tertiary accent |
| `muted` / `muted-foreground` | gray-100 / navy-200 | Subtle backgrounds, dimmed text |
| `accent` / `accent-foreground` | blue-300 / black | Accent highlights |
| `border` | gray-300 | All borders |
| `card` / `card-foreground` | white / black | Card surfaces |
| `destructive` / `destructive-background` | red-400 / red-100 | Error states |
| `success` / `success-background` | green-300 / green-100 | Success states |
| `warning` / `warning-background` | orange-300 / orange-100 | Warning states |
| `informative` / `informative-background` | blue-700 / blue-100 | Info states |

### Typography Scale

**Use these custom text classes** — not standard Tailwind `text-xl`, `text-2xl`, etc.:

| Class | Size | Weight | Usage |
|---|---|---|---|
| `text-h1` | 4rem / 64px | 500 | Page hero headings |
| `text-h2` | 3rem / 48px | 600 | Section headings |
| `text-h3` | 2.5rem / 40px | 500 | Sub-section headings |
| `text-h4` | 2rem / 32px | 600 | Card/widget headings |
| `text-h5` | 1.5rem / 24px | 500 | Small headings |
| `text-h6` | 1.25rem / 20px | 500 | Labels, sub-headings |
| `text-body` | 1rem / 16px | 400 | Body copy |
| `text-body-medium` | 1rem | 500 | Medium body |
| `text-body-semibold` | 1rem | 600 | Bold body |
| `text-body-sm` | 0.875rem / 14px | 400 | Small body |
| `text-body-sm-tight` | 0.875rem | 400 | Small body, tight (20px line-height) |
| `text-body-sm-medium` | 0.875rem | 500 | Small medium |
| `text-body-sm-semibold` | 0.875rem | 600 | Small bold |
| `text-caption` | 0.75rem / 12px | 400 | Captions |
| `text-caption-medium` | 0.75rem | 500 | Medium captions |
| `text-caption-semibold` | 0.75rem | 600 | Bold captions |
| `text-link` | 0.875rem | 600 | Link text |

**Responsive heading utilities** (scale down on mobile automatically):
- `text-heading-1` — h3 on mobile, h1 on md+
- `text-heading-2` — h4 on mobile, h3 on sm, h2 on md+
- `text-heading-3` — h5 on mobile, h3 on md+

### Custom Layout Utilities

```
h-fold         — height: calc(100svh - var(--total-header-height))
min-h-fold     — min-height version of above
top-fold       — top: var(--total-header-height) — for sticky elements below header
inset-fold     — inset: var(--total-header-height)
```

CSS variables: `--header-height: 4.5rem`, `--total-header-height: var(--header-height)`.

### Container

Custom `container` utility with responsive padding:
- Mobile: `px-4` (1rem)
- Desktop (lg+): `px-10` (2.5rem)
- Max width: 1440px (`--container-2xl`)

Usage: `<div className="container">...</div>`

### Shadows

- `shadow-subtle` — `0 2px 5px 0 rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05)` — very light card shadow

### Border Radius Aesthetic

The UI uses a rounded, pill/bubble aesthetic:
- **Buttons:** `rounded-full` (pill)
- **Inputs:** `rounded-full` (pill)
- **Cards:** `rounded-3xl` (very rounded)
- **Images inside cards:** `rounded-xl` or `rounded-2xl`
- **Hero/feature sections:** `rounded-[40px]`
- **Modals/dialogs:** `rounded-2xl` or `rounded-3xl`

### Dark Sections

Dark backgrounds use **navy colors** (`navy-500` through `navy-800`), not true black. Text on dark backgrounds is white:

```tsx
<section className="bg-navy-700 text-white">
```

### Gradient Patterns

```tsx
// Light gradient section
bg-linear-to-t from-purple-100 to-light-blue

// Dark section gradient
bg-linear-to-br from-navy-500 to-navy-700

// Hero image overlay
bg-linear-to-tl from-transparent to-black/30
```

