## shadcn/ui Components (`components/ui/`)

### Heavily Customized from Defaults

Do not assume default shadcn styles. Key customizations:

**Button** — pill shape (`rounded-full`), extra variants:
- Standard: `default`, `destructive`, `outline`, `secondary`, `ghost`, `link`
- Custom: `tertiary`, `teal`, `black`, `gray`, `carousel`
- Sizes: `default`, `sm`, `lg`, `icon`, `round` (circle), `link`

**Card** — `rounded-3xl` (very rounded corners)

**Input** — `rounded-full` (pill), `h-12` (48px height)

**Dialog** — `rounded-3xl`, custom close button with gray circle

**Badge** — extra variants: `tertiary`, `teal`, `black`, `gray`, `glass`, `informative`, `success`, `warning`, `destructive`

### Custom UI Components (not standard shadcn)

These exist in `components/ui/` — use them instead of building from scratch:
- `spinner.tsx` — Loading spinner
- `empty-state.tsx` — Empty state display
- `error-state.tsx` — Error state display
- `live-indicator.tsx` — Live data indicator dot
- `loading-overlay.tsx` — Full overlay loading state
- `animated-cta-button.tsx` — Animated call-to-action button
- `card-3d.tsx` — 3D tilt effect card
- `tags-input.tsx` — Multi-tag input
- `password-input.tsx` — Password with show/hide toggle
- `image-uploader.tsx` — Image upload with preview
- `typewriter-effect.tsx` — Typewriter text animation
- `code-reveal-effect.tsx` — Animated code reveal
- `code-block.tsx` — Syntax highlighted code block
- `sortable-header.tsx` — Table sortable column header

---

## Component Patterns

### Server vs Client Components

- **Default to Server Components** — no directive needed
- Add `"use client"` ONLY when you use:
  - React hooks (`useState`, `useEffect`, `useRef`, etc.)
  - Browser APIs (`window`, `document`, `localStorage`)
  - Event handlers (`onClick`, `onChange`, etc.)
  - Client-side libraries (motion/react, etc.)

### Props Typing

Always define explicit TypeScript interfaces:

```tsx
interface SectionProps {
  title: string;
  description?: string;
  className?: string;
  children: React.ReactNode;
}

export function Section({ title, description, className, children }: SectionProps) {
  return (
    <section className={cn("py-20", className)}>
      <h2 className="text-heading-2">{title}</h2>
      {description && <p className="text-body text-muted-foreground mt-4">{description}</p>}
      {children}
    </section>
  );
}
```

### The `cn()` Utility

Always use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional/merged class names. It uses an extended `tailwind-merge` that understands all custom text classes (`text-h1`, `text-body-medium`, etc.).

```tsx
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";

<div className={cn("base-classes", isActive && "active-class", className)} />
```

### Images

Always use `next/image`:

```tsx
import Image from "next/image";

// Fixed dimensions
<Image src="/images/logo.svg" alt="Logo" width={40} height={40} priority />

// Fill parent container
<div className="relative h-60 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-3xl">
  <Image src={url} alt={alt} fill className="object-cover" sizes="100vw" />
</div>
```

- Always include the `sizes` prop on fill images
- Add `priority` for above-the-fold images
- Add `draggable={false}` for decorative/logo images

### Sanity Images

Use the `urlForImage()` helper:

```tsx
import { urlForImage } from "@/lib/sanity/sanity-utils";

const imageUrl = urlForImage(sanityImageField)?.width(800).height(600).url();
```

Always null-check — `urlForImage` returns undefined if no asset.

### Links

```tsx
import Link from "next/link";

// Internal navigation — always use <Link>
<Link href="/explore" className="...">Explore</Link>

// External links — always add target and rel
<a href="https://external.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">External</a>
```

### Icons

**Lucide React** is the icon library:

```tsx
import { ArrowRight, ChevronDown, Menu, X } from "lucide-react";

<ArrowRight className="size-4" />
```

Custom social icons (Twitter/X, Instagram, Discord, LinkedIn) are in `components/social-icons.tsx`.

### Animations

Use **`motion/react`** (Framer Motion v11+):

```tsx
import { motion, AnimatePresence, useScroll, useTransform } from "motion/react";
```

**NOT `framer-motion`** — the package is `motion`.

Common patterns:
- Scroll-driven: `useScroll` + `useTransform`
- Entrance animations: `motion.div` with `initial/animate/exit`
- Stagger children: `transition: { staggerChildren: 0.1 }`
- Exit animations: wrap with `<AnimatePresence>`

---

## Sanity CMS Integration

### Key Files

```
app/(news)/sanity/lib/client.ts       — Sanity client
app/(news)/sanity/lib/live.ts         — sanityFetch + SanityLive
app/(news)/sanity/lib/queries.ts      — GROQ queries (defineQuery)
app/(news)/sanity/lib/sanity.types.ts — Auto-generated types (NEVER edit manually)
lib/sanity/api.ts                     — projectId, dataset, apiVersion
lib/sanity/sanity-utils.ts            — urlForImage(), resolveOpenGraphImage()
```

### Fetching Pattern

```tsx
import { sanityFetch } from "@/app/(news)/sanity/lib/live";
import { aboutPageQuery } from "@/app/(news)/sanity/lib/queries";

// In a server component
const { data } = await sanityFetch({ query: aboutPageQuery });
```

### GROQ Queries

```tsx
import { defineQuery } from "next-sanity";

export const aboutPageQuery = defineQuery(`*[_type == "aboutPage"][0]{
  heroHeadline,
  heroImage,
  teamGroups[]{
    _key,
    label,
    members[]->{ _id, name, role, image }  // reference expansion with ->
  }
}`);
```

### After Schema Changes

Run `pnpm sanity:typegen` to regenerate TypeScript types. Never edit `sanity.types.ts` by hand.

### Portable Text (Rich Content)

```tsx
import CustomPortableText from "@/components/blog/portable-text";

<CustomPortableText className="prose prose-custom mx-auto" value={post.body} />
```

The `prose-custom` utility (in `globals.css`) styles rich text with brand typography.

---

## Layout Patterns

### Root Layout (`app/layout.tsx`)

Renders the global shell: `<Header>`, `<main>`, `<ChatModal>`, `<Footer>`, `<Toaster>`. Wrapped in `<Providers>` (React Query + ThemeProvider forced to light).

### Providers (`app/providers.tsx`)

- `ThemeProvider` — **forced light mode** (`forcedTheme="light"`)
- `QueryClientProvider` — React Query

---

## Responsive Design

Standard Tailwind breakpoints, mobile-first:

| Breakpoint | Min-width | Key usage |
|---|---|---|
| `sm` | 640px | — |
| `md` | 768px | Tablet, responsive heading breakpoint |
| `lg` | 1024px | Desktop nav shows, container padding increases |
| `xl` | 1280px | — |
| `2xl` | 1440px | Max container width |

Mobile navigation shows at `< lg`. Desktop nav shows at `>= lg`.

---

## Common Mistakes to Avoid (Based on Real Examples)

These are real issues that came up during code review. Pay attention to these:

### 1. Don't put components inside route group folders

**Wrong:** Creating components in `app/(frontend)/about/scroll-reveal-text.tsx`
**Right:** Put them in `components/about/scroll-reveal-text.tsx`

Route folders (`app/`) should only contain `page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx`, and `not-found.tsx`. All reusable UI lives in `/components` organized by feature.

### 2. Don't use inline styles for typography

**Wrong:**
```tsx
<h1 style={{ fontSize: "clamp(36px, 6vw, 80px)", lineHeight: "1.05", letterSpacing: "-0.01em" }}>
```

**Right:**
```tsx
<h1 className="text-heading-1">
```

The project has a complete type scale (`text-h1` through `text-caption`) and responsive heading utilities (`text-heading-1/2/3`). Never use inline `style` for font sizes, line heights, or font weights — use the Tailwind classes.

### 3. Don't use inline styles for spacing/layout either

**Wrong:**
```tsx
<p style={{ fontSize: 20, lineHeight: "32px", letterSpacing: "-0.2px" }}>
```

**Right:**
```tsx
<p className="text-h6">
```

If the design calls for a size that's close to one of the scale values, use the closest scale value. The design system exists to maintain consistency.

### 4. Don't duplicate sub-components across files

**Wrong:** Defining the same `SectionLabel` component in both `page.tsx` and `team-section.tsx`.
**Right:** Extract shared components to their own file in the feature folder.

```tsx
// components/about/section-label.tsx
export function SectionLabel({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  return <p className="text-muted-foreground font-mono">{children}</p>;
}
```

### 5. Don't use custom padding instead of `container`

**Wrong:**
```tsx
<section className="px-5 sm:px-10 lg:px-20">
```

**Right:**
```tsx
<section className="container">
```

The `container` utility handles responsive padding consistently: `px-4` on mobile, `px-10` on lg+.

### 6. Don't use CSS `clamp()` for responsive sizing

**Wrong:**
```tsx
style={{ fontSize: "clamp(32px, 4vw, 48px)" }}
```

**Right:**
```tsx
className="text-heading-2" // or use responsive breakpoint classes
className="text-h4 md:text-h2"
```

Use the responsive heading utilities or explicit breakpoint classes. `clamp()` bypasses the design system and makes it hard to maintain consistency.

### 7. Don't use `type` for component props — use `interface`

**Wrong:**
```tsx
type WordProps = { word: string; progress: MotionValue<number>; range: [number, number] };
```

**Right:**
```tsx
interface WordProps { word: string; progress: MotionValue<number>; range: [number, number] }
```

The codebase consistently uses `interface` for component props.

### 8. Don't create inline SVG icons — check existing components first

**Wrong:** Writing a 20-line custom LinkedIn SVG inline in your component.
**Right:** Check `components/social-icons.tsx` — it already has Twitter/X, Instagram, Discord, and LinkedIn icons.

---

## Git Conventions

### Branch Naming

Always use a prefix with a slash: `prefix/kebab-case-description`

| Prefix | Usage |
|---|---|
| `feature/` | New features or pages — `feature/about-page`, `feature/admin-dashboard` |
| `fix/` | Bug fix branches — `fix/auth-redirect` |
| `refactor/` | Refactoring work — `refactor/query-keys` |
| `chore/` | Maintenance — `chore/dependency-updates` |

Special branches: `main` (production), `staging` (pre-production).

### Commit Messages

Use conventional commit format: `prefix(optional-scope): lowercase description`

| Prefix | Usage |
|---|---|
| `feat:` / `feat(scope):` | New features — `feat: about page`, `feat(lab): add admin test results table` |
| `fix:` / `fix(scope):` | Bug fixes — `fix: update calendar link and typo`, `fix(lab): sort results by sample` |
| `ui:` | UI-only changes — `ui: show mobile menu at lg breakpoint` |
| `refactor:` / `refactor(scope):` | Refactoring — `refactor(studio): query challenge data on the client` |
| `chore:` | Maintenance — `chore: format and lint` |
| `docs:` | Documentation — `docs: add frontend conventions guide` |

Rules:
- **Lowercase** description (no capital first letter)
- **No period** at the end
- Use `(scope)` when the change is scoped to a specific feature area (e.g., `lab`, `studio`, `cms`)
- Keep the description concise — explain the "what", not the "how"

---

## Things You Must NOT Do

1. **Don't use standard Tailwind color classes** like `text-blue-500`, `bg-red-200` — they don't exist. All colors are wiped and replaced with the brand palette.
2. **Don't use `text-xl`, `text-2xl`, etc. for headings** — use the semantic `text-h1` through `text-h6` scale or the responsive `text-heading-1/2/3` utilities.
3. **Don't add dark mode styles** — light mode is forced via ThemeProvider. There is no dark mode.
4. **Don't use `framer-motion`** — import from `motion/react` instead.
5. **Don't manually edit `sanity.types.ts`** — it's auto-generated. Run `pnpm sanity:typegen`.
6. **Don't create test files** — no testing infrastructure exists.
7. **Don't use server actions for reads** — server actions are POST only (mutations). Use fetch in `lib/data/` for GET operations.
8. **Don't add inline `<style>` tags or CSS modules** — all styling is done via Tailwind utility classes.
9. **Don't install new icon libraries** — use Lucide React (`lucide-react`) for icons.
10. **Don't add unnecessary `"use client"` directives** — default to server components.
11. **Don't use relative `../` imports across feature boundaries** — use `@/` for cross-feature imports (e.g., `components/lab` → `components/ui`). Relative `../` is fine within the same feature folder.

## Things You Should Always Do

1. **Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils`** for all conditional class merging.
2. **Use `next/image`** for all images, never bare `<img>` tags.
3. **Use `next/link`** for internal navigation, never bare `<a>` for internal routes.
4. **Use semantic color tokens** (`bg-primary`, `text-muted-foreground`) over raw colors when a semantic mapping exists.
5. **Use the custom text scale** (`text-h1`, `text-body-sm`, `text-caption`) for all typography.
6. **Use `container` class** for page-width content sections.
7. **Match the existing border-radius aesthetic** — pills for buttons/inputs, very rounded for cards.
8. **Check `components/ui/`** for existing components before building from scratch.
9. **Follow the import ordering convention** — Next.js, external libs, internal `@/` imports, relative imports, separated by blank lines.
10. **Use tabs for indentation** — the project uses tabs, not spaces.
